   - Verify: Returns status with phase, endpoint, conditions\n70: \n71: - [x] **T1.10** Implement `delete_agent_runtime()` method\n72:   - Delete CR via `delete_namespaced_custom_object()`\n73:   - Return status dict, handle 404 gracefully\n74:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n75:   - Verify: CR deleted, returns status\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ## Phase 2: KubernetesProvider Service Implementation ✓\n80: \n81: - [x] **T2.1** Create `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` file\n82:   - Import kubernetes client with availability check\n83:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n84:   - Verify: Module imports successfully\n85: \n86: - [x] **T2.2** Implement `KubernetesProvider.__init__()`\n87:   - Parameters: `namespace`, `verbose`, `kubeconfig`\n88:   - Initialize `_core_v1 = CoreV1Api()`, `_apps_v1 = AppsV1Api()`\n89:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n90:   - Verify: Instantiates with API clients\n91: \n92: - [x] **T2.3** Implement `_load_config()` method\n93:   - Same pattern as AgentCubeProvider\n94:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n95:   - Verify: Loads kubeconfig or in-cluster\n96: \n97: - [x] **T2.4** Implement `_ensure_namespace()` method\n98:   - Same pattern as AgentCubeProvider\n99:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n100:   - Verify: Creates namespace if needed\n101: \n102: - [x] **T2.5** Implement `deploy_agent()` method\n103:   - Parameters: `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `replicas`, `node_port`, `env_vars`\n104:   - Create Deployment + Service\n105:   - Wait for deployment ready\n106:   - Return deployment info dict\n107:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n108:   - Verify: Deployment + Service created, returns info\n109: \n110: - [x] **T2.6** Implement `_create_deployment()` method\n111:   - Build V1Deployment spec with container, env vars, replicas\n112:   - Handle 409 with replace\n113:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n114:   - Verify: Deployment created/updated\n115: \n116: - [x] **T2.7** Implement `_create_service()` method\n117:   - Build V1Service with NodePort type\n118:   - Handle 409 with replace\n119:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n120:   - Verify: Service created with correct node_port\n121: \n122: - [x] **T2.8** Implement `wait_for_deployment_ready()` method\n123:   - Poll deployment status.ready_replicas\n124:   - Timeout after specified seconds\n125:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n126:   - Verify: Returns when ready, raises TimeoutError\n127: \n128: - [x] **T2.9** Implement `get_agent_status()` method\n129:   - Read deployment, extract replica counts\n130:   - Return status dict\n131:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n132:   - Verify: Returns running/not_found status\n133: \n134: - [x] **T2.10** Implement `delete_agent()` method\n135:   - Delete deployment and service\n136:   - Handle 404 gracefully\n137:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n138:   - Verify: Resources deleted\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## Phase 3: PublishRuntime Integration ✓\n143: \n144: - [x] **T3.1** Import providers in `publish_runtime.py`\n145:   - Import `AgentCubeProvider`, `KubernetesProvider`\n146:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n147:   - Verify: Imports successful\n148: \n149: - [x] **T3.2** Add `provider` parameter to `PublishRuntime.__init__()`\n150:   - Default: `\"agentcube\"`\n151:   - Store as `self.provider`\n152:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n153:   - Verify: Runtime accepts provider parameter\n154: \n155: - [x] **T3.3** Implement `_validate_publish_prerequisites()` for AgentCube\n156:   - Check `workload_manager_url` and `router_url` in metadata\n157:   - Raise `ValueError` with helpful message if missing\n158:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n159:   - Verify: Validates URLs before deployment\n160: \n161: - [x] **T3.4** Implement `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` method\n162:   - Instantiate `AgentCubeProvider`\n163:   - Call `deploy_agent_runtime()` with metadata fields\n164:   - Call `wait_for_deployment_ready()`\n165:   - Call `get_agent_runtime_status()`\n166:   - Generate `session_id`, `agent_id`\n167:   - Return deployment info dict\n168:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n169:   - Verify: Returns complete deployment info\n170: \n171: - [x] **T3.5** Implement `_publish_k8s()` method\n172:   - Instantiate `KubernetesProvider`\n173:   - Validate `node_port` range (30000-32767)\n174:   - Call `deploy_agent()` with metadata fields\n175:   - Call `wait_for_deployment_ready()`\n176:   - Generate `session_id`\n177:   - Return deployment info dict\n178:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n179:   - Verify: Returns deployment + service info\n180: \n181: - [x] **T3.6** Implement `_build_agent_env_vars()` helper\n182:   - Extract `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `agent_endpoint` from metadata\n183:   - Return env dict\n184:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n185:   - Verify: Returns correct env vars\n186: \n187: - [x] **T3.7** Update `publish()` method to route by provider\n188:   - If `provider == \"agentcube\"`: call `_publish_cr_to_k8s()`\n189:   - If `provider == \"k8s\"`: call `_publish_k8s()`\n190:   - Else: raise `ValueError`\n191:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n192:   - Verify: Correct provider selected\n193: \n194: - [x] **T3.8** Implement `_update_publish_metadata()` method\n195:   - Update: `agent_id`, `session_id`, `agent_endpoint`, `image`, `k8s_deployment`\n196:   - Call `metadata_service.save_metadata()`\n197:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n198:   - Verify: Metadata persisted after publish\n199: \n200: - [x] **T3.9** Implement `_generate_session_id()` helper\n201:   - Generate 32-char alphanumeric using `secrets.choice()`\n202:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n203:   - Verify: Returns unique ID each call\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## Phase 4: CLI Integration ✓\n208: \n209: - [x] **T4.1** Add `provider` option to `publish` command\n210:   - `--provider` with default \"agentcube\"\n211:   - Help text: \"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"\n212:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n213:   - Verify: Option accepted, shown in --help\n214: \n215: - [x] **T4.2** Add `node_port` option to `publish` command\n216:   - `--node-port` (optional int)\n217:   - Help text: \"Specific NodePort (30000-32767)\"\n218:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n219:   - Verify: Option accepted\n220: \n221: - [x] **T4.3** Add `replicas` option to `publish` command\n222:   - `--replicas` (optional int, default 1)\n223:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n224:   - Verify: Option accepted\n225: \n226: - [x] **T4.4** Add `namespace` option to `publish` command\n227:   - `--namespace` (optional string)\n228:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n229:   - Verify: Option accepted\n230: \n231: - [x] **T4.5** Pass provider to `PublishRuntime` constructor\n232:   - `runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n233:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n234:   - Verify: Provider parameter passed through\n235: \n236: - [x] **T4.6** Pass all options to `runtime.publish()`\n237:   - Include: `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`\n238:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n239:   - Verify: Options dict complete\n240: \n241: - [x] **T4.7** Format output for AgentCube provider\n242:   - Show: Router URL, Workload Manager, Endpoint\n243:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n244:   - Verify: AgentCube-specific fields displayed\n245: \n246: - [x] **T4.8** Format output for K8s provider\n247:   - Show: Deployment, Service, NodePort, Service URL, Replicas\n248:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n249:   - Verify: K8s-specific fields displayed\n250: \n251: ---\n252: \n253: ## Phase 5: Validation & Edge Cases ✓\n254: \n255: - [x] **T5.1** Validate `workload_manager_url` and `router_url` for agentcube\n256:   - Check in metadata or raise ValueError\n257:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n258:   - Verify: Clear error message when URLs missing\n259: \n260: - [x] **T5.2** Validate `node_port` range (30000-32767)\n261:   - Validate in `_publish_k8s()` before provider call\n262:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n263:   - Verify: Rejects 29999 and 32768\n264: \n265: - [x] **T5.3** Handle existing AgentRuntime CR (409 conflict)\n266:   - Use `replace_namespaced_custom_object()` on 409\n267:   - Log update vs create\n268:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n269:   - Verify: Existing CR updated gracefully\n270: \n271: - [x] **T5.4** Handle existing Deployment/Service (409 conflict)\n272:   - Use `replace_namespaced_deployment()` and `replace_namespaced_service()`\n273:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n274:   - Verify: Existing resources updated\n275: \n276: - [x] **T5.5** Handle missing K8s config gracefully\n277:   - Try kubeconfig, then in-cluster, then raise RuntimeError\n278:   - File: Both providers\n279:   - Verify: Clear error when K8s unavailable\n280: \n281: - [x] **T5.6** Handle image push failures\n282:   - DockerService exceptions caught and re-raised with context\n283:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n284:   - Verify: Error message includes context\n285: \n286: ---\n287: \n288: ## Phase 6: Unit Tests ✓\n289: \n290: - [x] **T6.1** Test `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()`\n291:   - Mock kubernetes API, verify CR spec\n292:   - Test with/without workload_manager_url\n293:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n294:   - Verify: Correct CR created\n295: \n296: - [x] **T6.2** Test `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()`\n297:   - Mock kubernetes API, verify Deployment/Service spec\n298:   - Test node_port parameter\n299:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n300:   - Verify: Correct resources created\n301: \n302: - [x] **T6.3** Test `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()`\n303:   - Mock `AgentCubeProvider`, verify method calls\n304:   - Verify session_id generated\n305:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n306:   - Verify: Provider called correctly\n307: \n308: - [x] **T6.4** Test `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s()`\n309:   - Mock `KubernetesProvider`, verify method calls\n310:   - Verify node_port validated\n311:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n312:   - Verify: Provider called correctly\n313: \n314: - [x] **T6.5** Test node_port validation\n315:   - Test values: 29999, 30000, 32767, 32768\n316:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n317:   - Verify: Rejects out-of-range, accepts valid\n318: \n319: - [x] **T6.6** Test missing URLs for agentcube\n320:   - Call publish without workload_manager_url\n321:   - Verify ValueError with helpful message\n322:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n323:   - Verify: Clear error message\n324: \n325: - [x] **T6.7** Test provider routing\n326:   - Test provider=\"agentcube\" routes to CR method\n327:   - Test provider=\"k8s\" routes to K8s method\n328:   - Test provider=\"invalid\" raises ValueError\n329:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n330:   - Verify: Correct routing logic\n331: \n332: - [x] **T6.8** Test metadata update after publish\n333:   - Mock publish, verify metadata fields updated\n334:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n335:   - Verify: agent_id, session_id, endpoint saved\n336: \n337: ---\n338: \n339: ## Phase 7: Code Quality ✓\n340: \n341: - [x] **T7.1** Add docstrings to all public methods\n342:   - Document parameters, returns, raises\n343:   - File: Both providers, publish_runtime.py\n344:   - Verify: `help()` displays correctly\n345: \n346: - [x] **T7.2** Add type hints to all