{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875153843,"sessionID":"ses_28597ee40ffedwHk3wDZsgmjO5","part":{"id":"prt_d7a68557c001DfzCxp9bnjWc7h","messageID":"msg_d7a6842fd001YdGzLJW6pN4ylq","sessionID":"ses_28597ee40ffedwHk3wDZsgmjO5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1dbfa72c915d48a991b69b74","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.sdd_prompt.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.sdd_prompt.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: Write design.md with technical implementation details for the agentcube project:\n2: \n3: AR: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n4: Module: sdk-python\n5: Language: Python\n6: Size: M\n7: \n8: Specs:\n9: --- python-sdk/design.md ---\n10: # AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n11: \n12: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n13: \n14: ## Package layout\n15: \n16: | Path | Role |\n17: |------|------|\n18: | `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n19: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n20: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n21: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n22: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n23: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports client classes |\n24: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n25: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n26: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n27: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n28: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n29: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n30: | `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Empty (module marker) |\n31: | `examples/basic_usage.py`, `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`, `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`, `tests/*.py` | Non-library artifacts |\n32: \n33: ## Public exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n34: \n35: ```python\n36: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n37: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n38: \n39: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n40: ```\n41: \n42: `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` additionally exports (not in root `__all__`):\n43: \n44: ```python\n45: __all__ = [\n46:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n47:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n48:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n49: ]\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ## Configuration (no single `Configuration` class)\n53: \n54: There is **no** dedicated configuration dataclass. Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across:\n55: \n56: | Component | Resolved settings |\n57: |-----------|-------------------|\n58: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n59: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n60: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n61: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n62: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | same timeout defaults as above |\n63: \n64: ## `CodeInterpreterClient` (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n65: \n66: ```python\n67: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n68:     def __init__(\n69:         self,\n70:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n71:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n72:         ttl: int = 3600,\n73:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n74:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n75:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n76:         verbose: bool = False,\n77:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n78:     ): ...\n79: \n80:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None: ...\n81: \n82:     def __enter__(self): ...\n83:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n84: \n85:     def stop(self) -> None: ...\n86: \n87:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n88:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n89:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n90:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n91:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n92:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\"): ...\n93: ```\n94: \n95: **Fields set on instance:** `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `logger`, `cp_client`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n96: \n97: ## `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n98: \n99: ```python\n100: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n101:     def __init__(\n102:         self,\n103:         agent_name: str,\n104:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n105:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n106:         verbose: bool = False,\n107:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n108:         timeout: int = 120,\n109:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n110:     ): ...\n111: \n112:     def __enter__(self): ...\n113:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n114: \n115:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n116: \n117:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n118: ```\n119: \n120: **Fields:** `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `logger`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n121: \n122: ## `ControlPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n123: \n124: ```python\n125: class ControlPlaneClient:\n126:     def __init__(\n127:         self,\n128:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n129:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n130:         timeout: int = 120,\n131:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n132:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n133:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n134:     ): ...\n135: \n136:     def create_session(\n137:         self,\n138:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n139:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n140:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n141:         ttl: int = 3600,\n142:     ) -> str: ...\n143: \n144:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool: ...\n145: \n146:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n147: ```\n148: \n149: ### Control plane — HTTP\n150: \n151: | Method | Path | Notes |\n152: |--------|------|-------|\n153: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n154: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success in `delete_session` |\n155: \n156: **Headers (default on `self.session`):**\n157: \n158: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n159: - `Authorization`: `Bearer {token}` if token non-empty\n160: \n161: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n162: \n163: ## `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n164: \n165: ```python\n166: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n167:     def __init__(\n168:         self,\n169:         session_id: str,\n170:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n171:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n172:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n173:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n174:         timeout: int = 120,\n175:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n176:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n177:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n178:     ): ...\n179: \n180:     def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response: ...\n181: \n182:     def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n183:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n184:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n185:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n186:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n187:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any: ...\n188:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n189: ```\n190: \n191: ### Data plane (Code Interpreter) — base URL\n192: \n193: If `base_url` is not provided:\n194: \n195: ```text\n196: base_path = \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n197: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n198: ```\n199: \n200: ### Data plane — HTTP (relative to `self.base_url`)\n201: \n202: | Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n203: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n204: | `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n205: | `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n206: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n207: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download (`clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) |\n208: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` |\n209: \n210: **Headers:**\n211: \n212: - Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n213: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` when `body` is set in `_request`\n214: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type on the outer request)\n215: \n216: **Note:** Docstring states Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n217: \n218: ## `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n219: \n220: ```python\n221: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n222:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n223: \n224:     def __init__(\n225:         self,\n226:         router_url: str,\n227:         namespace: str,\n228:         agent_name: str,\n229:         timeout: int = 120,\n230:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n231:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n232:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n233:     ): ...\n234: \n235:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n236: \n237:     def invoke(\n238:         self,\n239:         session_id: str,\n240:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n241:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n242:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n243: \n244:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n245: ```\n246: \n247: ### Data plane (Agent Runtime) — base URL\n248: \n249: ```text\n250: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n251: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n252: ```\n253: \n254: ### Data plane — HTTP\n255: \n256: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n257: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n258: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | (session default headers only) | — |\n259: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n260: \n261: **Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is the method argument or `self.timeout`.\n262: \n263: ## `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n264: \n265: ```python\n266: def create_session(\n267:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n268:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n269: ) -> requests.Session: ...\n270: ```\n271: \n272: Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for `http://` and `https://`.\n273: \n274: ## `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n275: \n276: ```python\n277: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str: ...\n278: ```\n279: \n280: Returns file contents stripped, or `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n281: \n282: ## `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n283: \n284: ```python\n285: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger: ...\n286: ```\n287: \n288: ## Exception hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n289: \n290: ```python\n291: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n292:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n293:     pass\n294: \n295: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n296:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n297:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n298:         self.stderr = stderr\n299:         self.command = command\n300:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n301: \n302: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n303:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n304:     pass\n305: \n306: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n307:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n308:     pass\n309: ```\n310: \n311: ## Dependencies (`sdk-python/pyproject.toml`)\n312: \n313: ```toml\n314: dependencies = [\n315:     \"requests\",\n316:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n317:     \"cryptography\",\n318: ]\n319: ```\n320: \n321: - `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n322: - Build: `setuptools>=61.0`, `wheel`; backend `setuptools.build_meta`\n323: - Packages: `where = [\".\"]`, `include = [\"agentcube*\"]`, `namespaces = false`\n324: \n325: \n326: --- python-sdk/spec.md ---\n327: # AgentCube Python SDK Specification\n328: \n329: ## Purpose\n330: \n331: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n332: \n333: ## Requirements\n334: \n335: ### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n336: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n339: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n340: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n341: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n344: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n345: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n346: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n347: \n348: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n349: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n350: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n351: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n352: \n353: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter — execute, files, stop\n354: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n357: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n358: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n359: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n360: \n361: #### Scenario: Python code execution path\n362: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n363: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n364: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n365: \n366: ### Requirement: `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle\n367: The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL, then `POST` JSON payloads with session header.\n368: \n369: #### Scenario: Context manager\n370: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n371: - **WHEN** the block exits\n372: - **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n373: \n374: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session id\n375: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n376: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n377: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`; if missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: Invoke without session\n380: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy\n381: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n382: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n383: \n384: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — control plane\n385: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n386: \n387: #### Scenario: Create session\n388: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n389: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n390: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n391: \n392: #### Scenario: Delete session\n393: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n394: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n395: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and auth\n398: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n399: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n400: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n401: \n402: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n403: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n404: \n405: #### Scenario: Execute command\n406: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n407: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n408: \n409: #### Scenario: Files API\n410: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n411: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n412: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n413: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n414: \n415: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Agent Runtime)\n416: The system SHALL `POST` JSON to the invocation base URL with headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`.\n417: \n418: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n419: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)`\n420: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n421: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n422: \n423: ### Requirement: Session header management\n424: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests (`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` default session header; `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` uses class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`).\n425: \n426: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header\n427: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n428: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n429: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n430: \n431: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy\n432: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n433: \n434: #### Scenario: Command failure\n435: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n436: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n437: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n438: \n439: #### Scenario: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage\n440: - **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n441: - **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n442: - **THEN** these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n443: \n444: ### Requirement: Timeout behavior\n445: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n446: \n447: #### Scenario: Per-call override for code execution\n448: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n449: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n450: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n451: \n452: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient constructor timeouts\n453: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n454: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called without `timeout`\n455: - **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `120` (instance default)\n456: \n457: ---\n458: \n459: **Public package surface:** `agentcube/__init__.py` exports only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`.\n460: \n461: \n462: Previous proposal:\n463: [Stage ST-1 completed]\n464: \n465: Include: architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy.\n\n(End of file - total 465 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"Write design.md with technical implementation details for the agentcube project:\n\nAR: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\nModule: sdk-python\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\n\nSpecs:\n--- python-sdk/design.md ---\n# AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n\n## Package layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.sdd_prompt.md","time":{"start":1775875153820,"end":1775875153840}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875153845,"sessionID":"ses_28597ee40ffedwHk3wDZsgmjO5","part":{"id":"prt_d7a685ae7001EeerAqWD2hIv1M","messageID":"msg_d7a6842fd001YdGzLJW6pN4ylq","sessionID":"ses_28597ee40ffedwHk3wDZsgmjO5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b88b2c30a0f94468a5b446e6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_027.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_027.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal implements the `CodeInterpreterClient` for the AgentCube Python SDK (`sdk-python`). The goal is to:\n6: \n7: 1. **Provide high-level session management** - Abstract control plane session creation and data plane communication\n8: 2. **Enable code execution** - Execute Python code and shell commands in remote Code Interpreter sessions\n9: 3. **Support file operations** - Upload, download, write, and list files in the interpreter environment\n10: 4. **Ensure clean lifecycle** - Context manager protocol for automatic session cleanup and resource deallocation\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: **Module:** `sdk-python`  \n15: **Language:** Python  \n16: **Size:** M\n17: \n18: This AR covers:\n19: \n20: - **In scope:**\n21:   - `CodeInterpreterClient` class with context manager support\n22:   - `ControlPlaneClient` for session CRUD via Workload Manager\n23:   - `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` for data plane operations via Router\n24:   - Exception hierarchy (`AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`)\n25:   - HTTP session management with connection pooling\n26:   - Environment variable and file-based authentication token resolution\n27:   - `AgentRuntimeClient` for Agent Runtime invocations\n28: \n29: - **Out of scope:**\n30:   - Direct user-facing CLI commands (separate AR)\n31:   - Kubernetes CRD management (handled by CLI toolkit)\n32:   - Async/await HTTP client patterns\n33: \n34: ## Current State Analysis\n35: \n36: ### Existing Implementation\n37: \n38: Per the design specification (`python-sdk/design.md`), the following components are defined:\n39: \n40: 1. **Package Layout:**\n41:    - `agentcube/__init__.py` - Public exports (`CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient`)\n42:    - `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` - `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation\n43:    - `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` - `AgentRuntimeClient` implementation\n44:    - `agentcube/clients/` - Low-level HTTP clients\n45:    - `agentcube/utils/` - HTTP session, logging, token utilities\n46:    - `agentcube/exceptions.py` - Exception hierarchy\n47: \n48: 2. **Configuration Pattern:**\n49:    - No single `Configuration` class\n50:    - Distributed configuration: each client resolves its own settings from arguments or environment variables\n51: \n52: 3. **HTTP Contracts:**\n53:    - Control plane: `POST/DELETE {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`\n54:    - Data plane: `POST/GET {base_url}/api/*` (Router-relative paths)\n55: \n56: ### Issues Identified\n57: \n58: 1. **Session header naming** - Must use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` for consistency\n59: 2. **Timeout handling** - Read timeout needs +2.0s buffer to avoid premature `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124\n60: 3. **Exception usage** - `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` defined but not raised by core client modules\n61: \n62: ## Proposed Changes\n63: \n64: ### 1. Exception Hierarchy\n65: \n66: Implement in `agentcube/exceptions.py`:\n67: \n68: ```python\n69: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n70:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n71:     pass\n72: \n73: \n74: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n75:     \"\"\"Raised when a remote command fails with non-zero exit code.\"\"\"\n76:     \n77:     def __init__(self, exit_code: int, stderr: str, command: str = None):\n78:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n79:         self.stderr = stderr\n80:         self.command = command\n81:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n82: \n83: \n84: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n85:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n86:     pass\n87: \n88: \n89: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n90:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n91:     pass\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ### 2. ControlPlaneClient\n95: \n96: Implement in `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`:\n97: \n98: ```python\n99: class ControlPlaneClient:\n100:     def __init__(\n101:         self,\n102:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n103:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n104:         timeout: int = 120,\n105:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n106:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n107:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n108:     ):\n109:         self.base_url = workload_manager_url or os.getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")\n110:         if not self.base_url:\n111:             raise ValueError(\"workload_manager_url must be provided or set via WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")\n112:         \n113:         self.timeout = timeout\n114:         self.connect_timeout = connect_timeout\n115:         \n116:         # Resolve auth token\n117:         token = auth_token\n118:         if not token:\n119:             sa_token_path = \"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\"\n120:             token = read_token_from_file(sa_token_path)\n121:         \n122:         self.session = create_session(pool_connections=pool_connections, pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize)\n123:         self.session.headers[\"Content-Type\"] = \"application/json\"\n124:         if token:\n125:             self.session.headers[\"Authorization\"] = f\"Bearer {token}\"\n126:     \n127:     def create_session(\n128:         self,\n129:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n130:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n131:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n132:         ttl: int = 3600,\n133:     ) -> str:\n134:         \"\"\"Create a Code Interpreter session via Workload Manager.\"\"\"\n135:         url = f\"{self.base_url}/v1/code-interpreter\"\n136:         payload = {\n137:             \"name\": name,\n138:             \"namespace\": namespace,\n139:             \"ttl\": ttl,\n140:             \"metadata\": metadata or {},\n141:         }\n142:         response = self.session.post(\n143:             url,\n144:             json=payload,\n145:             timeout=(self.connect_timeout, self.timeout),\n146:         )\n147:         response.raise_for_status()\n148:         data = response.json()\n149:         session_id = data.get(\"sessionId\")\n150:         if not session_id:\n151:             raise ValueError(\"create_session response missing 'sessionId'\")\n152:         return session_id\n153:     \n154:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool:\n155:         \"\"\"Delete a Code Interpreter session. Returns True on success or 404.\"\"\"\n156:         url = f\"{self.base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}\"\n157:         try:\n158:             response = self.session.delete(\n159:                 url,\n160:                 timeout=(self.connect_timeout, self.timeout),\n161:             )\n162:             if response.status_code == 404:\n163:                 return True\n164:             response.raise_for_status()\n165:             return True\n166:         except requests.RequestException as e:\n167:             logger.warning(f\"delete_session failed: {e}\")\n168:             return False\n169:     \n170:     def close(self) -> None:\n171:         \"\"\"Close the HTTP session.\"\"\"\n172:         self.session.close()\n173: ```\n174: \n175: ### 3. CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n176: \n177: Implement in `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`:\n178: \n179: ```python\n180: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n181:     def __init__(\n182:         self,\n183:         session_id: str,\n184:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n185:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n186:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n187:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n188:         timeout: int = 120,\n189:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n190:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n191:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n192:     ):\n193:         self.session_id = session_id\n194:         self.timeout = timeout\n195:         self.connect_timeout = connect_timeout\n196:         \n197:         # Resolve base_url\n198:         if base_url:\n199:             self.base_url = base_url\n200:         else:\n201:             if not router_url or not namespace or not cr_name:\n202:                 raise ValueError(\"base_url or (router_url, namespace, cr_name) must be provided\")\n203:             base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n204:             self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n205:         \n206:         self.session = create_session(pool_connections=pool_connections, pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize)\n207:         self.session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"] = session_id\n208:     \n209:     def _request(\n210:         self,\n211:         method: str,\n212:         endpoint: str,\n213:         body: Optional[bytes] = None,\n214:         **kwargs,\n215:     ) -> requests.Response:\n216:         \"\"\"Internal request helper.\"\"\"\n217:         url = urljoin(self.base_url, endpoint)\n218:         headers = kwargs.pop(\"headers\", {})\n219:         if body:\n220:             headers[\"Content-Type\"] = \"application/json\"\n221:         \n222:         timeout = kwargs.pop(\"timeout\", (self.connect_timeout, self.timeout))\n223:         \n224:         response = self.session.request(\n225:             method,\n226:             url,\n227:             data=body,\n228:             headers=headers,\n229:             timeout=timeout,\n230:             **kwargs,\n231:         )\n232:         return response\n233:     \n234:     def execute_command(\n235:         self,\n236:         command: Union[str, List[str]],\n237:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n238:     ) -> str:\n239:         \"\"\"Execute a shell command in the Code Interpreter.\"\"\"\n240:         timeout_value = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n241:         \n242:         if isinstance(command, str):\n243:             command = [command]\n244:         \n245:         # Build timeout string for PicoD\n246:         timeout_str = f\"{int(timeout_value)}s\"\n247:         \n248:         # Calculate read timeout with buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout\n249:         read_timeout = timeout_value + 2.0 if isinstance(timeout_value, (int, float)) else timeout_value\n250:         \n251:         body = json.dumps({\n252:             \"command\": command,\n253:             \"timeout\": timeout_str,\n254:         }).encode(\"utf-8\")\n255:         \n256:         response = self._request(\n257:             \"POST\",\n258:             \"api/execute\",\n259:             body=body,\n260:             timeout=(self.connect_timeout, read_timeout),\n261:         )\n262:         response.raise_for_status()\n263:         data = response.json()\n264:         \n265:         exit_code = data.get(\"exit_code\", 0)\n266:         if exit_code != 0:\n267:             stderr = data.get(\"stderr\", \"Unknown error\")\n268:             raise CommandExecutionError(\n269:                 exit_code=exit_code,\n270:                 stderr=stderr,\n271:                 command=command,\n272:             )\n273:         \n274:         return data.get(\"stdout\", \"\")\n275:     \n276:     def run_code(\n277:         self,\n278:         language: str,\n279:         code: str,\n280:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n281:     ) -> str:\n282:         \"\"\"Execute code in the specified language.\"\"\"\n283:         if language.lower() in (\"python\", \"py\", \"python3\"):\n284:             # Write code to timestamped file\n285:             timestamp = datetime.utcnow().strftime(\"%Y%m%d%H%M%S%f\")\n286:             remote_path = f\"/tmp/code_{timestamp}.py\"\n287:             self.write_file(code, remote_path)\n288:             \n289:             # Execute via python3\n290:             return self.execute_command([\"python3\", remote_path], timeout=timeout)\n291:         else:\n292:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {language}\")\n293:     \n294:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n295:         \"\"\"Write file content via base64 encoding.\"\"\"\n296:         import base64\n297:         encoded = base64.b64encode(content.encode(\"utf-8\")).decode(\"utf-8\")\n298:         \n299:         body = json.dumps({\n300:             \"path\": remote_path,\n301:             \"content\": encoded,\n302:             \"mode\": \"0644\",\n303:         }).encode(\"utf-8\")\n304:         \n305:         response = self._request(\n306:             \"POST\",\n307:             \"api/files\",\n308:             body=body,\n309:         )\n310:         response.raise_for_status()\n311:     \n312:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n313:         \"\"\"Upload a file via multipart form.\"\"\"\n314:         with open(local_path, \"rb\") as f:\n315:             files = {\"file\": f}\n316:             data = {\n317:                 \"path\": remote_path,\n318:                 \"mode\": \"0644\",\n319:             }\n320:             \n321:             # Multipart upload - don't set Content-Type header\n322:             url = urljoin(self.base_url, \"api/files\")\n323:             response = self.session.post(\n324:                 url,\n325:                 files=files,\n326:                 data=data,\n327:                 headers={\"x-agentcube-session-id\": self.session_id},\n328:                 timeout=(self.connect_timeout, self.timeout),\n329:             )\n330:             response.raise_for_status()\n331:     \n332:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n333:         \"\"\"Download a file from the Code Interpreter.\"\"\"\n334:         clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")\n335:         response = self._request(\n336:             \"GET\",\n337:             f\"api/files/{clean_path}\",\n338:             stream=True,\n339:         )\n340:         response.raise_for_status()\n341:         \n342:         with open(local_path, \"wb\") as f:\n343:             for chunk in response.iter_content(chunk_size=8192):\n344:                 f.write(chunk)\n345:     \n346:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n347:         \"\"\"List files in a directory.\"\"\"\n348:         response = self._request(\n349:             \"GET\",\n350:             \"api/files\",\n351:             params={\"path\": path},\n352:         )\n353:         response.raise_for_status()\n354:         return response.json()\n355:     \n356:     def close(self) -> None:\n357:         \"\"\"Close the HTTP session.\"\"\"\n358:         self.session.close()\n359: ```\n360: \n361: ### 4. CodeInterpreterClient (High-Level Client)\n362: \n363: Implement in `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`:\n364: \n365: ```python\n366: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n367:     \"\"\"High-level client for Code Interpreter operations.\"\"\"\n368:     \n369:     def __init__(\n370:         self,\n371:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n372:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n373:         ttl: int = 3600,\n374:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n375:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n376:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n377:         verbose: bool = False,\n378:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n379:     ):\n380:         self.name = name\n381:         self.namespace = namespace\n382:         self.ttl = ttl\n383:         self.verbose = verbose\n384:         self.session_id = session_id\n385:         \n386:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n387:         \n388:         # Initialize control plane client\n389:         self.cp_client = ControlPlaneClient(\n390:             workload_manager_url=workload_manager_url,\n391:             auth_token=auth_token,\n392:         )\n393:         \n394:         # Resolve router URL\n395:         self.router_url = router_url or os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n396:         if not self.router_url:\n397:             raise ValueError(\"router_url must be provided or set via ROUTER_URL\")\n398:         \n399:         # Create session if session_id not provided\n400:         if not self.session_id:\n401:             self.session_id = self.cp_client.create_session(\n402:                 name=name,\n403:                 namespace=namespace,\n404:                 ttl=ttl,\n405:             )\n406:             self.logger.info(f\"Created session: {self.session_id}\")\n407:         \n408:         # Initialize data plane client\n409:         try:\n410:             self._init_data_plane()\n411:         except Exception as e:\n412:             # Cleanup on failure\n413:             self.logger.warning(f\"Data plane init failed: {e}, cleaning up session\")\n414:             self.cp_client.delete_session(self.session_id)\n415:             self.session_id = None\n416:             raise\n417:     \n418:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None:\n419:         \"\"\"Initialize the data plane client.\"\"\"\n420:         self.dp_client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n421:             session_id=self.session_id,\n422:             router_url=self.router_url,\n423:             namespace=self.namespace,\n424:             cr_name=self.name,\n425:         )\n426:     \n427:     def __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\":\n428:         return self\n429:     \n430:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n431:         self.stop()\n432:     \n433:     def stop(self) -> None:\n434:         \"\"\"Stop the Code Interpreter session.\"\"\"\n435:         self.logger.info(\"Stopping CodeInterpreterClient\")\n436:         \n437:         # Close data plane\n438:         if hasattr(self, \"dp_client\") and self.dp_client:\n439:             self.dp_client.close()\n440:         \n441:         # Delete control plane session\n442:         if self.session_id:\n443:             self.cp_client.delete_session(self.session_id)\n444:             self.logger.info(f\"Deleted session: {self.session_id}\")\n445:             self.session_id = None\n446:         \n447:         # Close control plane\n448:         self.cp_client.close()\n449:     \n450:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str:\n451:         \"\"\"Execute a shell command.\"\"\"\n452:         return self.dp_client.execute_command(command, timeout=timeout)\n453:     \n454:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str:\n455:         \"\"\"Execute code in the specified language.\"\"\"\n456:         return self.dp_client.run_code(language, code, timeout=timeout)\n457:     \n458:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n459:         \"\"\"Write file content.\"\"\"\n460:         self.dp_client.write_file(content, remote_path)\n461:     \n462:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n463:         \"\"\"Upload a file.\"\"\"\n464:         self.dp_client.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)\n465:     \n466:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n467:         \"\"\"Download a file.\"\"\"\n468:         self.dp_client.download_file(remote_path, local_path)\n469:     \n470:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n471:         \"\"\"List files in a directory.\"\"\"\n472:         return self.dp_client.list_files(path)\n473: ```\n474: \n475: ### 5. AgentRuntimeClient\n476: \n477: Implement in `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`:\n478: \n479: ```python\n480: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n481:     \"\"\"High-level client for Agent Runtime invocations.\"\"\"\n482:     \n483:     def __init__(\n484:         self,\n485:         agent_name: str,\n486:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n487:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n488:         verbose: bool = False,\n489:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n490:         timeout: int = 120,\n491:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n492:     ):\n493:         self.agent_name = agent_name\n494:         self.namespace = namespace\n495:         self.timeout = timeout\n496:         self.connect_timeout = connect_timeout\n497:         self.session_id = session_id\n498:         \n499:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n500:         \n501:         # Resolve router URL\n502:         self.router_url = router_url or os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n503:         if not self.router_url:\n504:             raise ValueError(\"router_url must be provided or set via ROUTER_URL\")\n505:         \n506:         # Bootstrap session_id if not provided\n507:         if not self.session_id:\n508:             self._bootstrap_session_id()\n509:         \n510:         # Initialize data plane client\n511:         self.dp_client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n512:             router_url=self.router_url,\n513:             namespace=self.namespace,\n514:             agent_name=self.agent_name,\n515:             timeout=self.timeout,\n516:             connect_timeout=self.connect_timeout,\n517:         )\n518:     \n519:     def _bootstrap_session_id(self) -> None:\n520:         \"\"\"Bootstrap session_id from Agent Runtime invocation endpoint.\"\"\"\n521:         base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{self.namespace}/agent-runtimes/{self.agent_name}/invocations/\"\n522:         base_url = urljoin(self.router_url, base_path)\n523:         \n524:         session = create_session()\n525:         try:\n526:             response = session.get(\n527:                 base_url,\n528:                 timeout=(self.connect_timeout, self.timeout),\n529:             )\n530:             response.raise_for_status()\n531:             \n532:             self.session_id = response.headers.get(\"x-agentcube-session-id\")\n533:             if not self.session_id:\n534:                 raise ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")\n535:             \n536:             self.logger.info(f\"Bootstrapped session_id: {self.session_id}\")\n537:         finally:\n538:             session.close()\n539:     \n540:     def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\":\n541:         return self\n542:     \n543:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n544:         self.close()\n545:     \n546:     def invoke(\n547:         self,\n548:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n549:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n550:     ) -> Any:\n551:         \"\"\"Invoke the Agent Runtime with a JSON payload.\"\"\"\n552:         if not self.session_id:\n553:             raise ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")\n554:         \n555:         timeout_value = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n556:         \n557:         response = self.dp_client.invoke(\n558:             session_id=self.session_id,\n559:             payload=payload,\n560:             timeout=timeout_value,\n561:         )\n562:         response.raise_for_status()\n563:         return response.json()\n564:     \n565:     def close(self) -> None:\n566:         \"\"\"Close the Agent Runtime client.\"\"\"\n567:         self.logger.info(\"Closing AgentRuntimeClient\")\n568:         if hasattr(self, \"dp_client\") and self.dp_client:\n569:             self.dp_client.close()\n570: ```\n571: \n572: ### 6. AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n573: \n574: Implement in `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`:\n575: \n576: ```python\n577: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n578:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n579:     \n580:     def __init__(\n581:         self,\n582:         router_url: str,\n583:         namespace: str,\n584:         agent_name: str,\n585:         timeout: int = 120,\n586:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n587:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n588:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n589:     ):\n590:         self.router_url = router_url\n591:         self.namespace = namespace\n592:         self.agent_name = agent_name\n593:         self.timeout = timeout\n594:         self.connect_timeout = connect_timeout\n595:         \n596:         base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n597:         self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n598:         \n599:         self.session = create_session(pool_connections=pool_connections, pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize)\n600:     \n601:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n602:         \"\"\"Bootstrap session_id via GET request.\"\"\"\n603:         response = self.session.get(\n604:             self.base_url,\n605:             timeout=(self.connect_timeout, self.timeout),\n606:         )\n607:         response.raise_for_status()\n608:         \n609:         session_id = response.headers.get(self.SESSION_HEADER)\n610:         if not session_id:\n611:             raise ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")\n612:         \n613:         return session_id\n614:     \n615:     def invoke(\n616:         self,\n617:         session_id: str,\n618:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n619:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n620:     ) -> requests.Response:\n621:         \"\"\"Invoke the Agent Runtime with a JSON payload.\"\"\"\n622:         self.session.headers[self.SESSION_HEADER] = session_id\n623:         self.session.headers[\"Content-Type\"] = \"application/json\"\n624:         \n625:         timeout_value = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n626:         \n627:         response = self.session.post(\n628:             self.base_url,\n629:             json=payload,\n630:             timeout=(self.connect_timeout, timeout_value),\n631:         )\n632:         return response\n633:     \n634:     def close(self) -> None:\n635:         \"\"\"Close the HTTP session.\"\"\"\n636:         self.session.close()\n637: ```\n638: \n639: ### 7. Utility Functions\n640: \n641: Implement in `agentcube/utils/http.py`:\n642: \n643: ```python\n644: def create_session(\n645:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n646:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n647: ) -> requests.Session:\n648:     \"\"\"Create a requests Session with connection pooling.\"\"\"\n649:     session = requests.Session()\n650:     adapter = requests.adapters.HTTPAdapter(\n651:         pool_connections=pool_connections,\n652:         pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize,\n653:     )\n654:     session.mount(\"http://\", adapter)\n655:     session.mount(\"https://\", adapter)\n656:     return session\n657: ```\n658: \n659: Implement in `agentcube/utils/utils.py`:\n660: \n661: ```python\n662: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n663:     \"\"\"Read token from file, returning empty string on FileNotFoundError.\"\"\"\n664:     try:\n665:         with open(file_path, \"r\") as f:\n666:             return f.read().strip()\n667:     except FileNotFoundError:\n668:         return \"\"\n669: ```\n670: \n671: Implement in `agentcube/utils/log.py`:\n672: \n673: ```python\n674: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n675:     \"\"\"Get a logger with the specified name and level.\"\"\"\n676:     logger = logging.getLogger(name)\n677:     logger.setLevel(level)\n678:     \n679:     if not logger.handlers:\n680:         handler = logging.StreamHandler()\n681:         handler.setLevel(level)\n682:         formatter = logging.Formatter(\n683:             \"%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s\"\n684:         )\n685:         handler.setFormatter(formatter)\n686:         logger.addHandler(handler)\n687:     \n688:     return logger\n689: ```\n690: \n691: ### 8. Package Configuration\n692: \n693: Create `pyproject.toml`:\n694: \n695: ```toml\n696: [build-system]\n697: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n698: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n699: \n700: [project]\n701: name = \"agentcube-sdk\"\n702: version = \"0.1.0\"\n703: description = \"AgentCube Python SDK for Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime\"\n704: readme = \"README.md\"\n705: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n706: dependencies = [\n707:     \"requests\",\n708:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n709:     \"cryptography\",\n710: ]\n711: \n712: [tool.setuptools.packages.find]\n713: where = [\".\"]\n714: include = [\"agentcube*\"]\n715: namespaces = false\n716: ```\n717: \n718: ### 9. Module Exports\n719: \n720: Implement `agentcube/__init__.py`:\n721: \n722: ```python\n723: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n724: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n725: \n726: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n727: ```\n728: \n729: Implement `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`:\n730: \n731: ```python\n732: from .control_plane import ControlPlaneClient\n733: from .code_interpreter_data_plane import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n734: from .agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n735: \n736: __all__ = [\n737:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n738:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n739:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n740: ]\n741: ```\n742: \n743: ## Impact Analysis\n744: \n745: ### Files to Create\n746: \n747: | File | Purpose |\n748: |------|---------|\n749: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n750: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n751: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n752: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Client re-exports |\n753: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | Control plane HTTP client |\n754: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | Code Interpreter data plane client |\n755: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Agent Runtime data plane client |\n756: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | HTTP session factory |\n757: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Token reading utility |\n758: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | Logger factory |\n759: | `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Module marker |\n760: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy |\n761: | `pyproject.toml` | Package configuration |\n762: \n763: ### Dependencies\n764: \n765: - `requests` - HTTP client\n766: - `PyJWT>=2.0.0` - JWT handling (future extensibility)\n767: - `cryptography` - Cryptographic primitives (future extensibility)\n768: - Python >= 3.10\n769: \n770: ### Backward Compatibility\n771: \n772: This is a new feature with no existing users. No backward compatibility concerns.\n773: \n774: ### Testing Impact\n775: \n776: Test files should cover:\n777: \n778: - Context manager lifecycle and cleanup (`__enter__`, `__exit__`, `stop()`)\n779: - Session creation/deletion flows with control plane\n780: - Command execution with non-zero exit codes (raises `CommandExecutionError`)\n781: - File upload/download/write/list operations\n782: - Error handling (data plane init failure, missing URLs)\n783: - Environment variable fallback behavior (`ROUTER_URL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`)\n784: - Timeout handling with buffer (+2.0s for read timeout)\n785: \n786: ## Alternatives Considered\n787: \n788: ### Alternative 1: Single Configuration Class\n789: \n790: **Approach:** Create a dedicated `Configuration` dataclass to hold all settings.\n791: \n792: **Pros:**\n793: - Centralized configuration management\n794: - Easier to validate at initialization\n795: \n796: **Cons:**\n797: - Adds unnecessary abstraction\n798: - Less flexible for per-client customization\n799: - More boilerplate\n800: \n801: **Decision:** Rejected. Distributed configuration pattern is simpler and aligns with spec.\n802: \n803: ### Alternative 2: Async HTTP Client\n804: \n805: **Approach:** Use `aiohttp` or `httpx` for async operations.\n806: \n807: **Pros:**\n808: - Better performance for concurrent operations\n809: - Modern async API\n810: \n811: **Cons:**\n812: - Increased complexity for users\n813: - Additional dependency burden\n814: - Not required for typical use cases\n815: \n816: **Decision:** Rejected. Synchronous `requests` is sufficient and simpler.\n817: \n818: ### Alternative 3: Automatic Session Reuse\n819: \n820: **Approach:** Automatically detect and reuse existing sessions by name/namespace.\n821: \n822: **Pros:**\n823: - Could reduce session creation overhead\n824: \n825: **Cons:**\n826: - Adds complexity\n827: - Potential for unintended session reuse\n828: - TTL-based cleanup becomes ambiguous\n829: \n830: **Decision:** Rejected. Explicit `session_id` parameter provides clearer control.\n831: \n832: ## Implementation Checklist\n833: \n834: - [ ] Create package structure (directories and `__init__.py` files)\n835: - [ ] Implement utility functions (http, utils, log)\n836: - [ ] Implement exception hierarchy\n837: - [ ] Implement `ControlPlaneClient`\n838: - [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n839: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n840: - [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterClient` with context manager\n841: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` with context manager\n842: - [ ] Create `pyproject.toml` with dependencies\n843: - [ ] Write unit tests for all clients\n844: - [ ] Write integration tests for session lifecycle\n845: - [ ] Create example usage scripts\n846: \n847: ## Testing Strategy\n848: \n849: ### Unit Tests\n850: \n851: ```python\n852: # tests/test_code_interpreter.py\n853: \n854: class TestCodeInterpreterClient:\n855:     def test_context_manager_cleanup(self, mock_clients):\n856:         with CodeInterpreterClient(\n857:             router_url=\"http://test\",\n858:             workload_manager_url=\"http://wm\",\n859:         ) as client:\n860:             pass\n861:         \n862:         mock_clients.cp_client.delete_session.assert_called_once()\n863:         mock_clients.cp_client.close.assert_called_once()\n864:         mock_clients.dp_client.close.assert_called_once()\n865:     \n866:     def test_missing_router_url_raises(self):\n867:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"router_url must be provided\"):\n868:             CodeInterpreterClient()\n869:     \n870:     def test_execute_command_nonzero_exit(self, mock_dp_client):\n871:         mock_dp_client.execute_command.side_effect = CommandExecutionError(\n872:             exit_code=1,\n873:             stderr=\"error message\",\n874:             command=[\"ls\", \"nonexistent\"],\n875:         )\n876:         \n877:         client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n878:             router_url=\"http://test\",\n879:             session_id=\"test-session\",\n880:         )\n881:         \n882:         with pytest.raises(CommandExecutionError) as exc_info:\n883:             client.execute_command(\"ls nonexistent\")\n884:         \n885:         assert exc_info.value.exit_code == 1\n886: ```\n887: \n888: ### Integration Tests\n889: \n890: ```python\n891: # tests/test_integration.py\n892: \n893: class TestIntegration:\n894:     @pytest.mark.skipif(not os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\"), reason=\"Requires ROUTER_URL\")\n895:     def test_full_lifecycle(self):\n896:         with CodeInterpreterClient(\n897:             name=\"test-interpreter\",\n898:             namespace=\"default\",\n899:             ttl=300,\n900:         ) as client:\n901:             # Execute command\n902:             result = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n903:             assert \"hello\" in result\n904:             \n905:             # Write and execute Python code\n906:             code = \"print('test output')\"\n907:             result = client.run_code(\"python\", code)\n908:             assert \"test output\" in result\n909:             \n910:             # File operations\n911:             client.write_file(\"file content\", \"/tmp/test.txt\")\n912:             files = client.list_files(\"/tmp\")\n913:             assert any(\"test.txt\" in f for f in files)\n914: ```\n915: \n916: ## Future Considerations\n917: \n918: 1. **Async support** - Add `AsyncCodeInterpreterClient` for async use cases\n919: 2. **Streaming output** - Support streaming stdout/stderr for long-running commands\n920: 3. **Session persistence** - Allow saving/restoring session state\n921: 4. **Batch operations** - Execute multiple commands in a single request\n922: 5. **Advanced file operations** - Support for directories, symlinks, permissions\n923: 6. **Language extensions** - Support for more languages (JavaScript, Go, etc.)\n924: \n925: ## References\n926: \n927: - Python SDK Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n928: - Python SDK Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n929: - Requests Documentation: https://requests.readthedocs.io/\n930: - Pydantic Documentation: https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n931: \n932: ## Acceptance Criteria\n933: \n934: | Criterion | Verification |\n935: |-----------|--------------|\n936: | `CodeInterpreterClient` creates session | Control plane `create_session` called when `session_id` not provided |\n937: | Context manager cleans up | `__exit__` calls `stop()`, deletes session, closes HTTP sessions |\n938: | Command execution works | `execute_command` returns stdout on success |\n939: | Non-zero exit raises | `CommandExecutionError` raised with exit_code, stderr |\n940: | File operations work | `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files` functional |\n941: | Router URL validation | `ValueError` raised if `router_url` and `ROUTER_URL` both missing |\n942: | Session header correct | `x-agentcube-session-id` used (lowercase) |\n943: | Timeout buffer applied | Read timeout = request timeout + 2.0s |\n944: | `AgentRuntimeClient` bootstraps | GET invocation endpoint to obtain `session_id` |\n945: | Package installs | `pip install .` succeeds, imports work |\n946: \n947: ---\n948: \n949: **Document Version:** 1.0  \n950: **Last Updated:** 2026-04-11  \n951: **Author:** AgentCube Team  \n952: **Contact:** agentcube@volcano.sh  \n953: **AR:** AR-027  \n954: **Module:** `sdk-python`\n\n(End of file - total 954 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the `CodeInterpreterClient` for the AgentCube Python SDK (`sdk-python`). The goal is to:\n\n1. **Provide high-level session management** - Abstract control plane session creation and data plane communication\n2. **Enable code execution** - Execute Python code and shell commands in remote Code Interpreter sessions\n3. **Support file operations** - Upload, download, write, and list files in the interpreter environment\n4. **Ensure clean lifecycle** - Context manager protocol for automatic session cleanup and resource deallocation\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_027.md","time":{"start":1775875153823,"end":1775875153843}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875153850,"sessionID":"ses_28597ee40ffedwHk3wDZsgmjO5","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6850b7001fGcMp9jLS0M2T9","messageID":"msg_d7a6842fd001YdGzLJW6pN4ylq","sessionID":"ses_28597ee40ffedwHk3wDZsgmjO5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7140942a9b6745aa9da21022","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n2: \n3: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n4: \n5: ## Architecture\n6: \n7: ### Overview\n8: \n9: The AgentCube Python SDK follows a layered architecture with clear separation between control plane and data plane operations:\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                    Public API Layer                          │\n14: │  CodeInterpreterClient          AgentRuntimeClient          │\n15: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n16:                               │\n17:         ┌─────────────────────┴─────────────────────┐\n18:         │                                           │\n19:         ▼                                           ▼\n20: ┌───────────────────┐                   ┌───────────────────────┐\n21: │   Control Plane   │                   │     Data Plane        │\n22: │  ControlPlane     │                   │  CodeInterpreter      │\n23: │     Client        │                   │  DataPlaneClient      │\n24: │                   │                   │                       │\n25: │  (Session Mgmt)   │                   │  (Code/File Ops)      │\n26: └───────────────────┘                   └───────────────────────┘\n27:                                                  │\n28:                               ┌──────────────────┴──────────────┐\n29:                               │                                 │\n30:                               ▼                                 ▼\n31:                     ┌───────────────────┐           ┌───────────────────┐\n32:                     │   AgentRuntime    │           │    HTTP Client    │\n33:                     │  DataPlaneClient  │           │   Utilities       │\n34:                     │                   │           │                   │\n35:                     │  (Agent Invoke)   │           │  (Session, Auth)  │\n36:                     └───────────────────┘           └───────────────────┘\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ### Component Responsibilities\n40: \n41: | Component | Responsibility |\n42: |-----------|---------------|\n43: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | High-level facade for code interpretation; orchestrates control plane session lifecycle and data plane operations |\n44: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | High-level facade for agent runtime invocations; manages session bootstrapping and payload delivery |\n45: | `ControlPlaneClient` | Control plane HTTP client; session creation/deletion via Workload Manager |\n46: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Data plane HTTP client; code execution and file operations via Router |\n47: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane HTTP client; agent invocation via Router |\n48: | `create_session` | HTTP session factory with connection pooling |\n49: | `read_token_from_file` | Service account token loading utility |\n50: | `get_logger` | Structured logging configuration |\n51: \n52: ### Design Patterns\n53: \n54: 1. **Facade Pattern**: `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` provide simplified interfaces to complex subsystems\n55: 2. **Context Manager Protocol**: Both high-level clients support `with` statement for automatic resource cleanup\n56: 3. **Dependency Injection**: Lower-level clients are instantiated by higher-level clients with resolved configuration\n57: 4. **Environment Configuration**: Settings resolve from constructor args → environment variables → defaults\n58: \n59: ## Data Structures\n60: \n61: ### Class Instance Attributes\n62: \n63: #### `CodeInterpreterClient`\n64: \n65: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n66: |-----------|------|-------------|\n67: | `name` | `str` | Interpreter session name (default: `\"my-interpreter\"`) |\n68: | `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace (default: `\"default\"`) |\n69: | `ttl` | `int` | Session time-to-live in seconds (default: `3600`) |\n70: | `verbose` | `bool` | Enable debug logging |\n71: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n72: | `cp_client` | `ControlPlaneClient` | Control plane client instance |\n73: | `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL |\n74: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session identifier (provided or created) |\n75: | `dp_client` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Data plane client instance |\n76: \n77: #### `AgentRuntimeClient`\n78: \n79: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n80: |-----------|------|-------------|\n81: | `agent_name` | `str` | Target agent runtime name |\n82: | `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace |\n83: | `timeout` | `int` | Default request timeout in seconds (default: `120`) |\n84: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout in seconds (default: `5.0`) |\n85: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n86: | `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL |\n87: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session identifier (bootstrapped or provided) |\n88: | `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane client instance |\n89: \n90: #### `ControlPlaneClient`\n91: \n92: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n93: |-----------|------|-------------|\n94: | `base_url` | `str` | Workload Manager API base URL |\n95: | `auth_token` | `str` | Bearer token for authentication |\n96: | `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (default: `120`) |\n97: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n98: | `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with connection pooling |\n99: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n100: \n101: #### `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n102: \n103: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n104: |-----------|------|-------------|\n105: | `session_id` | `str` | Session identifier for header |\n106: | `base_url` | `str` | Computed Router invocation URL |\n107: | `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (default: `120`) |\n108: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n109: | `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with connection pooling |\n110: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n111: \n112: #### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n113: \n114: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n115: |-----------|------|-------------|\n116: | `base_url` | `str` | Computed Router invocation URL |\n117: | `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (default: `120`) |\n118: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n119: | `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with connection pooling |\n120: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n121: \n122: ### Exception Classes\n123: \n124: ```\n125: AgentCubeError (base)\n126: ├── CommandExecutionError\n127: │   ├── exit_code: int\n128: │   ├── stderr: str\n129: │   └── command: Optional[str]\n130: ├── SessionError\n131: └── DataPlaneError\n132: ```\n133: \n134: | Exception | Raised When |\n135: |-----------|-------------|\n136: | `AgentCubeError` | Base class; not raised directly |\n137: | `CommandExecutionError` | Remote command returns non-zero exit code |\n138: | `SessionError` | Reserved for session creation/management failures |\n139: | `DataPlaneError` | Reserved for data plane operation failures |\n140: \n141: ### Request/Response DTOs\n142: \n143: #### Control Plane - Create Session Request\n144: \n145: ```json\n146: {\n147:   \"name\": \"string\",\n148:   \"namespace\": \"string\",\n149:   \"ttl\": 3600,\n150:   \"metadata\": {}\n151: }\n152: ```\n153: \n154: #### Control Plane - Create Session Response\n155: \n156: ```json\n157: {\n158:   \"sessionId\": \"string\"\n159: }\n160: ```\n161: \n162: #### Data Plane - Execute Command Request\n163: \n164: ```json\n165: {\n166:   \"command\": [\"string\"] | \"string\",\n167:   \"timeout\": \"120s\"\n168: }\n169: ```\n170: \n171: #### Data Plane - Execute Command Response\n172: \n173: ```json\n174: {\n175:   \"stdout\": \"string\",\n176:   \"stderr\": \"string\",\n177:   \"exit_code\": 0\n178: }\n179: ```\n180: \n181: #### Data Plane - Write File Request\n182: \n183: ```json\n184: {\n185:   \"path\": \"string\",\n186:   \"content\": \"base64-encoded-string\",\n187:   \"mode\": \"0644\"\n188: }\n189: ```\n190: \n191: #### Data Plane - List Files Response\n192: \n193: ```json\n194: {\n195:   \"files\": [\"string\"]\n196: }\n197: ```\n198: \n199: ## API Contracts\n200: \n201: ### Control Plane API (Workload Manager)\n202: \n203: | Operation | HTTP Method | URL Pattern | Request Body | Response |\n204: |-----------|-------------|-------------|--------------|----------|\n205: | Create Session | POST | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | `CreateSessionRequest` | `sessionId: str` |\n206: | Delete Session | DELETE | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | - | `bool` |\n207: \n208: #### Create Session\n209: \n210: - **URL**: `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`\n211: - **Method**: `POST`\n212: - **Headers**:\n213:   - `Content-Type: application/json`\n214:   - `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token present)\n215: - **Body**:\n216:   ```json\n217:   {\n218:     \"name\": \"my-interpreter\",\n219:     \"namespace\": \"default\",\n220:     \"ttl\": 3600,\n221:     \"metadata\": {}\n222:   }\n223:   ```\n224: - **Success Response** (200/201):\n225:   ```json\n226:   {\n227:     \"sessionId\": \"ci-abc123\"\n228:   }\n229:   ```\n230: - **Timeout**: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple\n231: \n232: #### Delete Session\n233: \n234: - **URL**: `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n235: - **Method**: `DELETE`\n236: - **Headers**: Same as Create Session\n237: - **Success Response** (200/204): `True`\n238: - **Not Found** (404): `True` (treated as idempotent success)\n239: - **Other Errors**: Log and return `False`\n240: \n241: ### Data Plane API (Code Interpreter via Router)\n242: \n243: | Operation | HTTP Method | URL Pattern | Request Body | Response |\n244: |-----------|-------------|-------------|--------------|----------|\n245: | Execute Command | POST | `{base_url}api/execute` | `ExecuteCommandRequest` | `str` (stdout) |\n246: | Run Code | POST | `{base_url}api/execute` | `ExecuteCommandRequest` | `str` (stdout) |\n247: | Write File | POST | `{base_url}api/files` | `WriteFileRequest` (JSON) | `None` |\n248: | Upload File | POST | `{base_url}api/files` | Multipart form | `None` |\n249: | Download File | GET | `{base_url}api/files/{path}` | - | `bytes` |\n250: | List Files | GET | `{base_url}api/files` | Query: `path` | `List[str]` |\n251: \n252: #### Execute Command\n253: \n254: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/execute`\n255: - **Method**: `POST`\n256: - **Headers**:\n257:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n258:   - `Content-Type: application/json`\n259: - **Body**:\n260:   ```json\n261:   {\n262:     \"command\": [\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print('hello')\"],\n263:     \"timeout\": \"120s\"\n264:   }\n265:   ```\n266: - **Success Response** (200): stdout string\n267: - **Error Response**: Raises `CommandExecutionError` if `exit_code != 0`\n268: - **Timeout**: `(connect_timeout, timeout_value + 2.0)` for read side\n269: \n270: #### Write File\n271: \n272: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/files`\n273: - **Method**: `POST`\n274: - **Headers**:\n275:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n276:   - `Content-Type: application/json`\n277: - **Body**:\n278:   ```json\n279:   {\n280:     \"path\": \"/app/test.py\",\n281:     \"content\": \"<base64-encoded>\",\n282:     \"mode\": \"0644\"\n283:   }\n284:   ```\n285: \n286: #### Upload File (Multipart)\n287: \n288: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/files`\n289: - **Method**: `POST`\n290: - **Headers**:\n291:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n292: - **Form Data**:\n293:   - `file`: binary file content\n294:   - `path`: remote file path\n295:   - `mode`: file mode (default: `\"0644\"`)\n296: \n297: #### Download File\n298: \n299: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/files/{clean_path}` where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n300: - **Method**: `GET`\n301: - **Headers**:\n302:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n303: - **Query Params**: `stream=True`\n304: - **Response**: Binary file content\n305: \n306: #### List Files\n307: \n308: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/files`\n309: - **Method**: `GET`\n310: - **Headers**:\n311:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n312: - **Query Params**: `path` (default: `\".\"`)\n313: - **Response**: JSON array of file paths\n314: \n315: ### Data Plane API (Agent Runtime via Router)\n316: \n317: | Operation | HTTP Method | URL Pattern | Request Body | Response |\n318: |-----------|-------------|-------------|--------------|----------|\n319: | Bootstrap Session | GET | `{base_url}` | - | `x-agentcube-session-id` header |\n320: | Invoke Agent | POST | `{base_url}` | `Dict[str, Any]` | `requests.Response` |\n321: \n322: #### Bootstrap Session ID\n323: \n324: - **URL**: `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n325: - **Method**: `GET`\n326: - **Headers**: None (session default only)\n327: - **Success Response**: Header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n328: - **Error**: Raises `ValueError` if header missing\n329: \n330: #### Invoke Agent\n331: \n332: - **URL**: `{base_url}`\n333: - **Method**: `POST`\n334: - **Headers**:\n335:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n336:   - `Content-Type: application/json`\n337: - **Body**: JSON payload dict\n338: - **Timeout**: `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n339: \n340: ## Error Handling\n341: \n342: ### Exception Hierarchy\n343: \n344: ```python\n345: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n346:     \"\"\"Base exception for all AgentCube SDK errors\"\"\"\n347:     pass\n348: \n349: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n350:     \"\"\"Raised when remote command execution fails\"\"\"\n351:     def __init__(self, exit_code: int, stderr: str, command: Optional[str] = None):\n352:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n353:         self.stderr = stderr\n354:         self.command = command\n355:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n356: \n357: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n358:     \"\"\"Reserved for session creation/management failures\"\"\"\n359:     pass\n360: \n361: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n362:     \"\"\"Reserved for data plane operation failures\"\"\"\n363:     pass\n364: ```\n365: \n366: ### Error Handling Strategy\n367: \n368: | Component | Error Source | Handling Strategy |\n369: |-----------|--------------|-------------------|\n370: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `_init_data_plane()` failure | Log warning, delete session, re-raise |\n371: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | Context manager exit | Call `stop()` for cleanup regardless of exception |\n372: | `execute_command` | Non-zero exit code | Raise `CommandExecutionError` |\n373: | `ControlPlaneClient` | 404 on delete | Return `True` (idempotent) |\n374: | `ControlPlaneClient` | Other HTTP errors | Log and return `False` |\n375: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | Missing session header | Raise `ValueError` |\n376: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | Invoke without session | Raise `ValueError` |\n377: | HTTP clients | `requests.RequestException` | Propagate to caller |\n378: \n379: ### Cleanup Guarantees\n380: \n381: 1. **Context Manager Protocol**: Both `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` implement `__enter__` and `__exit__` for deterministic cleanup\n382: 2. **Stop Method**: `CodeInterpreterClient.stop()` ensures:\n383:    - Data plane session closure\n384:    - Control plane session deletion (if created internally)\n385:    - HTTP session close\n386: 3. **Close Method**: `AgentRuntimeClient.close()` ensures HTTP session closure\n387: 4. **Exception Safety**: Cleanup occurs regardless of exception type in `__exit__`\n388: \n389: ## Testing Strategy\n390: \n391: ### Test Categories\n392: \n393: | Category | Scope | Tools | Location |\n394: |----------|-------|-------|----------|\n395: | Unit Tests | Individual classes/methods | `pytest`, `unittest.mock` | `tests/unit/` |\n396: | Integration Tests | Client-server interaction | `pytest`, test fixtures | `tests/integration/` |\n397: | End-to-End Tests | Full workflow validation | `pytest`, live environment | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` |\n398: \n399: ### Unit Test Strategy\n400: \n401: #### Mocking Approach\n402: \n403: ```python\n404: from unittest.mock import Mock, patch, MagicMock\n405: import pytest\n406: \n407: # Example: Mock HTTP session\n408: @pytest.fixture\n409: def mock_session():\n410:     session = Mock(spec=requests.Session)\n411:     session.post.return_value.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"test-123\"}\n412:     return session\n413: \n414: # Example: Patch create_session\n415: @patch('agentcube.utils.http.create_session')\n416: def test_control_plane_create_session(mock_create_session):\n417:     mock_session = Mock()\n418:     mock_session.post.return_value.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"test-123\"}\n419:     mock_create_session.return_value = mock_session\n420:     \n421:     client = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://test\")\n422:     session_id = client.create_session()\n423:     \n424:     assert session_id == \"test-123\"\n425: ```\n426: \n427: #### Test Coverage Targets\n428: \n429: | Module | Coverage Target | Key Scenarios |\n430: |--------|-----------------|---------------|\n431: | `code_interpreter.py` | 90% | Context manager, session lifecycle, delegation |\n432: | `agent_runtime.py` | 90% | Bootstrap, invoke, context manager |\n433: | `control_plane.py` | 95% | HTTP request construction, error handling |\n434: | `code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | 95% | URL construction, timeout logic, file operations |\n435: | `agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | 95% | Session bootstrap, invoke |\n436: | `utils/` | 100% | Session creation, token reading, logging |\n437: | `exceptions.py` | 100% | Exception initialization |\n438: \n439: ### Integration Test Strategy\n440: \n441: #### Test Fixtures\n442: \n443: ```python\n444: @pytest.fixture\n445: def code_interpreter_client():\n446:     client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n447:         router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"),\n448:         workload_manager_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"),\n449:         namespace=\"test\"\n450:     )\n451:     yield client\n452:     client.stop()\n453: \n454: @pytest.fixture\n455: def agent_runtime_client():\n456:     client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n457:         agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n458:         router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"),\n459:         namespace=\"test\"\n460:     )\n461:     yield client\n462:     client.close()\n463: ```\n464: \n465: #### Integration Test Scenarios\n466: \n467: | Test | Steps | Expected Outcome |\n468: |------|-------|------------------|\n469: | `test_code_execution` | Create session → Execute `print(\"hello\")` | stdout contains \"hello\" |\n470: | `test_file_operations` | Write file → List files → Download file | File exists, content matches |\n471: | `test_agent_invoke` | Bootstrap session → Invoke agent | Valid response from agent |\n472: \n473: ### End-to-End Test\n474: \n475: Located at `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`:\n476: \n477: ```python\n478: #!/usr/bin/env python3\n479: \"\"\"End-to-end test for Code Interpreter with PicoD\"\"\"\n480: \n481: import sys\n482: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n483: \n484: def main():\n485:     with CodeInterpreterClient(\n486:         router_url=\"http://localhost:8080\",\n487:         namespace=\"default\"\n488:     ) as client:\n489:         # Test 1: Simple command\n490:         result = client.execute_command(\"echo 'hello'\")\n491:         assert \"hello\" in result\n492:         \n493:         # Test 2: Python code\n494:         result = client.run_code(\"python\", \"print(2 + 2)\")\n495:         assert \"4\" in result\n496:         \n497:         # Test 3: File write and read\n498:         client.write_file(\"test content\", \"/app/test.txt\")\n499:         result = client.execute_command(\"cat /app/test.txt\")\n500:         assert \"test content\" in result\n501:         \n502:     print(\"All E2E tests passed!\")\n503:     return 0\n504: \n505: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n506:     sys.exit(main())\n507: ```\n508: \n509: ### Continuous Integration\n510: \n511: | Pipeline Stage | Tests | Environment |\n512: |----------------|-------|-------------|\n513: | Lint | `pytest --flake8`, `mypy` | Isolated |\n514: | Unit Test | `pytest tests/unit/` | Isolated |\n515: | Integration Test | `pytest tests/integration/` | Test cluster |\n516: | E2E Test | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` | Staging environment |\n517: \n518: ## Dependencies\n519: \n520: ### Runtime Dependencies\n521: \n522: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n523: |---------|---------|---------|\n524: | `requests` | `>=2.28.0` | HTTP client |\n525: | `PyJWT` | `>=2.0.0` | JWT token handling |\n526: | `cryptography` | `>=38.0.0` | Cryptographic operations |\n527: \n528: ### Build Configuration\n529: \n530: ```toml\n531: [build-system]\n532: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n533: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n534: \n535: [project]\n536: name = \"agentcube-sdk\"\n537: version = \"0.1.0\"\n538: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n539: dependencies = [\n540:     \"requests\",\n541:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n542:     \"cryptography\",\n543: ]\n544: \n545: [tool.setuptools.packages.find]\n546: where = [\".\"]\n547: include = [\"agentcube*\"]\n548: namespaces = false\n549: ```\n550: \n551: ### Development Dependencies\n552: \n553: | Package | Purpose |\n554: |---------|---------|\n555: | `pytest` | Test framework |\n556: | `pytest-mock` | Mocking utilities |\n557: | `pytest-cov` | Coverage reporting |\n558: | `mypy` | Static type checking |\n559: | `flake8` | Code style linting |\n560: | `black` | Code formatting |\n561: \n562: ## Logging Strategy\n563: \n564: ### Logger Configuration\n565: \n566: ```python\n567: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n568:     logger = logging.getLogger(name)\n569:     logger.setLevel(level)\n570:     \n571:     if not logger.handlers:\n572:         handler = logging.StreamHandler()\n573:         formatter = logging.Formatter(\n574:             '%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s'\n575:         )\n576:         handler.setFormatter(formatter)\n577:         logger.addHandler(handler)\n578:     \n579:     return logger\n580: ```\n581: \n582: ### Log Levels\n583: \n584: | Level | Usage |\n585: |-------|-------|\n586: | `DEBUG` | HTTP request/response details, configuration resolution |\n587: | `INFO` | Session creation/deletion, major lifecycle events |\n588: | `WARNING` | Non-critical errors (404 on delete), fallback behavior |\n589: | `ERROR` | Operation failures, exceptions |\n590: \n591: ### Example Log Output\n592: \n593: ```\n594: 2024-01-15 10:30:00 - agentcube.code_interpreter - INFO - Creating session: my-interpreter\n595: 2024-01-15 10:30:01 - agentcube.control_plane - DEBUG - POST http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter\n596: 2024-01-15 10:30:01 - agentcube.code_interpreter - INFO - Session created: ci-abc123\n597: 2024-01-15 10:30:02 - agentcube.data_plane - DEBUG - POST http://router:8080/.../api/execute\n598: ```\n599: \n600: ## Security Considerations\n601: \n602: ### Authentication\n603: \n604: 1. **Control Plane**: Bearer token via `Authorization` header\n605:    - Token from constructor argument `auth_token`\n606:    - Fallback to service account token file: `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n607: \n608: 2. **Data Plane**: JWT handled by Router; SDK does not set `Authorization` header\n609: \n610: ### Session ID Security\n611: \n612: - Session ID transmitted in `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n613: - Session ID should be treated as sensitive (grants access to sandbox)\n614: - Automatic session cleanup on context manager exit\n615: \n616: ### File Operations\n617: \n618: - No local file system access outside provided paths\n619: - Upload/download operations require explicit local path specification\n620: - Remote file paths validated/cleaned before use\n\n(End of file - total 620 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Overview\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK follows a layered architecture with clear separation between control plane and data plane operations:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Public API Layer                          │\n│  CodeInterpreterClient          AgentRuntimeClient          │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n        ┌─────────────────────┴─────────────────────┐\n        │                                           │\n        ▼                                           ▼\n┌───────────────────┐                   ┌───────────────────────┐","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/design.md","time":{"start":1775875153815,"end":1775875153847}}}}
