 `stop()`, deletes session, closes HTTP sessions\n3. ✅ `execute_command()` returns stdout on success\n4. ✅ `CommandExecutionError` raised with `exit_code`, `stderr` on non-zero exit\n5. ✅ File operations (`write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`) functional\n6. ✅ Router URL validation: `ValueError` if both arg and `ROUTER_URL` missing\n7. ✅ Session header uses lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`\n8. ✅ Read timeout buffer (+2.0s) applied to `execute_command()`\n9. ✅ `AgentRuntimeClient` bootstraps session ID via GET invocation endpoint\n10. ✅ `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()` raises `ValueError` if session_id not initialized\n11. ✅ Control plane handles 404 as idempotent success on delete\n12. ✅ Data plane init failure triggers session cleanup and re-raise\n13. ✅ Package installs via `pip install .`\n14. ✅ Imports work: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient`\n15. ✅ Unit tests cover all clients and error cases (>= 80% coverage)\n16. ✅ Integration tests pass in live environment\n17. ✅ Type hints pass mypy validation\n18. ✅ Code passes ruff/flake8 linting\n19. ✅ Examples provided and runnable\n20. ✅ README documents installation and usage\n\n---\n\n**Notes:**\n- Stage ST-3 marked complete: all clients and tests implemented\n- Session header naming: uses lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` throughout\n- Timeout handling: read timeout gets +2.0s buffer to avoid premature `ReadTimeout`\n- Exception usage: `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` defined but not raised by core clients (reserved for future use)\n- Distributed configuration: no single `Configuration` class; each client resolves own settings\n\n(End of file)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-027/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T16321